- Option/Some/None pattern gives us way to handles null values properly without throwing NullPointerException
- Also it is quite handy for Exception Handling 
  - https://github.com/AmolKakade/ScalaPreparation/blob/master/Theory-ExceptionHandling

var a:Option[String] = Some("Amol")
var b:Option[String] = None
println(a.getOrElse("..."))  // Outcomes Amol
println(b.getOrElse("..."))  // Outcomes ...
